{
  "abstract": "Management of rain water is the key to success in dryland agriculture as\r\nmost of the cultivated areas in India as well as in the entire world\r\ndepends on rainfed farming. An integrated approach for the management\r\nof rain water consists of increasing moisture storage in the soil, optimum\r\nuse of this moisture through efficient cropping systems, harvesting a\r\nportion of the runoff water for \"life saving\" irrigation, and reorientating\r\nthe concepts and organization of irrigation, including that from tanks, to\r\nenhance productivity per unit of rain water.",
